# ORIG TITLE    Bosnian Federation President detained for bribery . 
# ORIG CONTENT  Bosnia’s autonomous Muslim-Croat federation president, Zivko Budimir, has been sentenced by a court for taking bribes to arrange pardons for convicts. He will be detained for a month with four other officials as he’s been declared a flight risk. His Party of Justice and Trust has accused state prosecutors of “meddling in politics”. 
